  "name": "Luke 11:1–13",
  "localizedName": "Luke 11:1–13",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The disciples saw how important prayer was in Jesus’ life. They wanted to learn to pray like Jesus did. The words of the prayer Jesus taught them are bold."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus’ disciples are to call God their Father. They should ask for God’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108225",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "name"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to be honoured all over the world. They can trust that God is bringing his kingdom and should desire more of it."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus told the disciples to ask God for daily bread. He was talking about more than bread that people bake and eat. In John 6:32 Jesus is called the true bread from heaven. This means that life comes through Jesus. Jesus makes it possible for people to have life that can’t be destroyed."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus’ disciples should pray for their sins to be forgiven. And they should ask God for help to remain faithful. They need his help to say no to sin when they are tempted."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus then told some stories about prayer. These stories showed that God wants prayer to be an important part of his children’s lives."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
